  "prompt": "What is kidney function test?",
  "response": "A kidney function test is a series of medical examinations used to assess how well the kidneys are working. These tests typically include:\n\n1. Blood Tests:\n- Creatinine level\n- Blood Urea Nitrogen (BUN)\n- Glomerular Filtration Rate (GFR)\n- Electrolyte levels\n\n2. Urine Tests:\n- Urinalysis\n- Protein and albumin levels\n- Creatinine clearance\n- Microalbuminuria test\n\n3. Purpose of these tests:\n- Evaluate kidney health\n- Detect kidney disease\n- Monitor existing kidney conditions\n- Check for kidney damage\n- Assess overall kidney function\n\n4. What these tests can reveal:\n- Kidney disease\n- Kidney damage\n- Reduced kidney function\n- Potential kidney problems\n- Kidney stone risk\n- Diabetes-related kidney issues\n\n5. When these tests are recommended:\n- Regular health check-ups\n- Diabetes screening\n- High blood pressure monitoring\n- Family history of kidney disease\n- Symptoms of kidney problems\n\nThese tests help healthcare professionals diagnose and manage kidney-related health conditions effectively.",
